<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="FO4" checkit-title="Exact First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
        Explain why one of the following ODEs is exact, and why the other is not.
    </p>
      <me>20 \, t^{3} + 2 \, t y^{2} - 5 \, y = -20 \, y^{3} {y'} - t^{2} {y'} - 10 \, t y {y'}</me><me>2 \, t y - 5 \, t {y'} - 5 \, y = -20 \, t^{3} - t^{2} {y'}</me>
    <p>
      Then find an implicit solution for the exact ODE
      that satisfies the initial value
        <m>y(-1)=1</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>The following ODE is exact.</p>
      <me>2 \, t y - 5 \, t {y'} - 5 \, y = -20 \, t^{3} - t^{2} {y'}</me>
    <p>
      Its implicit solution satisfying the initial value is:
    </p>
      <me>5 \, t^{4} + t^{2} y - 5 \, t y = 11</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
